<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albright Visits Romania with Dollar Promise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 22 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright arrived in here Tuesday for a three-hour visit.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Albright and Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu discussed bilateral ties, the Kosovo situation and
cooperation between Romania and NATO.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Albright thanked Constantinescu for Romania'
s strong support for the Kosovo operation, stressing that
Bucharest's attitude mattered to the US.
</P>
<P>
The Secretary also said that she was aware of the economic
problems caused by the Kosovo conflict. She assured the Romanian
president that the United States would help with the economic
recovery, and the Congress would approve more money in this regard.
</P>
<P>
This is Albright's second stop, after visiting Bulgaria, in a
series of visits to countries surrounding Yugoslavia that have
suffered economic losses during the 78-day allied airstrike
campaign.
</P>
<P>
Her visit to Romania was postponed two weeks ago due to the
prolonged Bonn talks that were aimed at solving the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
