<HEADLINE> Vaughters Wins Route du Sud Cycle Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 22 (Xinhua) -- American sprint champion Jonathan
Vaughters won his first professional career title on Tuesday when
he took the Route du Sud cycling race.
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old, second in the Dauphine Criterium cycling event
earlier this month, was aided by compatriot and world champion
Lance Armstrong, over the fourth and last stage.
</P>
<P>
Vaughters, who was seventh in the world time-trial championship
last year, won the time-trial third stage of the Dauphine
Criterium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
