<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Perrier Vittel to Explore More Opportunities in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Perrier Vittel, the largest
bottled-water manufacturer in the world, is to invest more than 50
million U.S. dollars in China over the next three years, Xinhua
learned here in Hong Kong Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Among the first moves is the construction of a new plant in
Shanghai, where a ground-breaking ceremony was held last Friday (
June 18).
</P>
<P>
A member of the Nestle' Group, Perrier Vittel S.A. is planning
to move aggressively into China as well as the rest of Asia. The
manufacturing investment for Asia in the next four years amounts
to 150 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Taking into account the investment in marketing and
distribution, the total amount exceeds 200 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
"Our long term objective is to become market leader in bottled
water in China and Asia, and develop strong brand equity in the
region," said Garth Britton, Director for the Asia Zone of Perrier
Vittel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
