<DOCNO> XIE19990622.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thirty-one Charged in Doping Investigation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 22 (Xinhua) -- French justice Tuesday said 31
people linked to cycling -- former professionals, amateur riders
and officials -- had been charged in an investigation over an
alleged dope dealing network known as the "Belgian pot case".
</P>
<P>
The prosecutor of Poitiers said investigating magistrate Marc
Bauhain had recently been hearing the main defendants in the case.
</P>
<P>
The investigation is looking into allegations of widespread
doping in amateur cycling near Poitiers, in central France,
including claims that riders frequently took "Belgian pot" -- a
mixture of caffeine and amphetamines.
</P>
<P>
It is also probing allegations that dealers had offered another
mixture, dubbed "Polish pot", in which heroin and cocaine were to
be found.
</P>
<P>
The 31 were placed under investigation on various doping
charges and face sentences of up to 10 years in jail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
