<DOCNO> XIE19990622.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Five UIA Architecture Exhibitions Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Five architecture exhibitions
connected with the 20th World Congress of the International Union
of Architects (UIA) opened here today in the newly-built Center of
Chinese Architecture Culture.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China,
chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference and honorary chairman of the
Organizing Committee of the 20th World Congress of the UIA, and
Sara Topelson Ginberg, president of the UIA, cut the ribbon for
the opening ceremony, and visited the exhibitions later.
</P>
<P>
The exhibitions include a Chinese architecture exhibition,
architecture exhibition of UIA member states, photo exhibition of
ancient Chinese architecture, Chinese Children's painting
exhibition and exhibition of ancient Chinese windows and doors.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese architecture exhibition, the first of its kind ever
held in China, displays the development of Chinese architecture
over the past 5,000 years and its modern achievements, while the
international part focuses on the recent achievements of
architects from 32 countries.
</P>
<P>
The 20th World Congress of the UIA is scheduled to open here
Wednesday, and several thousand architects from more than 100
countries are expected to attend it.
</P>
<P>
This evening, the Beijing Municipal People's Government and the
city's planning commission gave a reception for those attending
the 20th UIA World Congress to be scheduled on June 23-26 here in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The congress is held every three years, and this is the first
time for it to be convened in an Asian country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
