<DOCNO> XIE19990622.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eritrea Denies Occupying of Ethiopian Soil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a letter dated June 16 to the U.N. Security Council released
Tuesday, Eritrean Foreign Minister Haile Woldensae said that
Eritrea is "not occupying any Ethiopian land."
</P>
<P>
A report from the Organization of United Africa (OAU) has
recently called on Eritrea to withdraw from all Ethiopian
territories seized in a year-old border war.
</P>
<P>
The Eritrean Foreign Minister said that "Ethiopia violated the
U.S. brokered moratorium on air strikes and targeted civilian
areas in Eritrea".
</P>
<P>
The statement said that Ethiopia had expelled Eritrea's
ambassador to the OAU, which is headquartered in the capital of
Ethiopia, and ransacked his residence.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopia-Eritrea war broke out in early May 1998 along the
1,000- kilometer borders of the two Horn of African neighbors.
</P>
<P>
Although both countries have agreed to the peace framework put
forward by the OAU, they differed over the details of the peace
plan and its implementation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
