<HEADLINE> China, Russia to Boost Economic, Trade Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- In the eyes of Zhong Fushou,
deputy secretary-general of east China's port city of Taizhou
Governemtn, Russia is a big market full of business opportunities.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his point of view at a Sino-Russian seminar on
regional cooperation oriented toward the 21st century, which ended
here today.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day gathering, businessmen from central,
southern and coastal parts of China showed great interest in
expanding economic and trade cooperation with Russia, in addition
to those from the areas of China's border with Russia.
</P>
<P>
Taizhou, known as a center for the manufacture of daily
necessities, hopes to establish a solely- or jointly-invested
trade center in Elektrostal near Moscow, to help meet Russia's
demand for shoes, leather goods and garments.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, it also hopes to introduce Russia's advanced
technology in the pharmaceuticals and chemicals sectors, and
import Russian timber and other raw materials.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Russian participants also expressed willingness
to further cooperate with their Chinese counterparts. Deputy Mayor
of Elektrostal Y.A. Tokmachev will travel to Taizhou tomorrow to
discuss ways to promote economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Anhui, Hunan, Hubei and Guizhou provinces also
want to cooperate with Russia in industrial development.
</P>
<P>
Yantai, a port city in the coastal province of Shandong, has
begun to set up a Sino-Russian high-tech cooperation center, to
concentrate on electronic information, new materials,
pharmaceuticals and fine chemicals.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Governor of Novosibirsk V.P. Nekhoroshkov, who attended
the seminar, said that Sino-Russian cooperation in high technology
will improve the two countries' trade structure, and boost
bilateral economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Manzhouli, the largest land trade port in China, together with
Russia's Chita Oblast, are planning to set up a border trade
complex, where individuals and enterprises will be encouraged to
engage in industry, trade, tourism and entertainment.
</P>
<P>
Mayor Yang Hanzhong of Manzhouli told the seminar that the
establishment of such a trade complex will help make full use of
the resources, raw materials and preferential policies of the two
countries, to achieve the maximum economic results.
</P>
<P>
Participants said that localities in the two countries should
increase mutual understanding. The establishment of sister cities
will help promote exchanges of information, and guarantee the
smooth implementation of cooperative projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
