<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: China's Stock Market Recovers From Two-Year Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The Composite Stock Index of the
Shanghai Stock Exchange finished today at a historic high of 1564.
44 points, a clear indication that China's stock market has
recovered from the bearish situation of the last two years.
</P>
<P>
The new high, which has been widely expected by the market for
the last few days, is a natural development of the bullish rally
starting on May 19.
</P>
<P>
Since then, the indices of the Shanghai and Shenzhen stock
exchanges have soared by more than 40 percent.
</P>
<P>
On June 17, the turnover of the two exchanges hit a record high
of 52.18 billion yuan, up 1,300 percent from the figure for May 18.
</P>
<P>
The rally came amid a spate of good news from the part of the
government, including the approval for a major securities firm to
expand its capital base, reducing the stamp tax on B- share
trading from four to three percent and a major cut in the interest
rate.
</P>
<P>
While most investors were still hesitating, the ``People's
Daily" gave its blessing to the market surge in a front-page
special commentator's article on June 15.
</P>
<P>
The article pointed out that the recent rally is a reflection
of the macroeconomic situation and a result of the market
operation mechanism, adding that it is only the beginning of a
long-term development.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the editorial greatly boosted investors'
confidence.
</P>
<P>
Xu Tong, an analyst at Citic Securities Ltd, said the current
rally is reasonable and different from market bubbles or
overheating.
</P>
<P>
He gave two reasons: One is that most of the funds have been
flowing to high-tech stocks and blue chips, indicating that the
investors are cautious. The other is that the current rate of
change is only 10 percent, which is within the normal range.
</P>
<P>
He noted that an active stock market will be greatly helpful
for China's reform of its state-owned sector and the stimulation
of the domestic market, and hence boost the growth of the national
economy.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Zhengqing, chairman of the China Securities Regulatory
Commission, said on Monday that the current rally marks a turning
point from which a regularized and vigorous stock market will
march into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Stock analysts here predicted that the market will continue to
surge in the near future, and the market indices are sure to hit
new highs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
