<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Trading Hits New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Stock trading on the Shanghai
Stock Exchange (SSE) soared to a historic high today, amid an
ongoing bullish mood buoyed up by the authorities' encouraging
words in recent weeks.
</P>
<P>
The SSE Stock Index opened at 1551.8 points, once touched the
day's bottom of 1524.4 points, and closed at a new high of 1564.44
points, compared with the historic figure of 1558 points achieved
six years ago.
</P>
<P>
Today's trading volume was 23.87 billion yuan, slightly down
day-on-day.
</P>
<P>
Local observers attributed the bullish mood in the stock
business to official encouragement, including the May 19 editorial
in the ``People's Daily" and a recent speech by Zhou Zhengqing,
chairman of the China Securities Regulatory Commission.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Zhou said the buoyant market indicates the
reality of the macro-economy in China and the internal
requirements by the market. He expressed his confidence that the
Chinese stock market has laid a foundation for long-term, stable
development.
</P>
<P>
Zhou's remark is an objective evaluation of the stock market
and an optimistic forecast of the future of the market, the
observers noted.
</P>
<P>
Some local stock dealers called it a result of the present
situation, as the Securities Law is to go into force by July and
the government has taken a series of measures that are favorable
to the stock business.
</P>
<P>
They agree that securities traders should make the most of the
current situation by abiding by the law, standardizing their
practice and perfecting their internal management. 
</P>
</TEXT>
