attention from the central government and people of all walks of
life.
</P>
<P>
It pointed out that China's pollution problem can not be solved
in a short period of time, and a long-term program is required to
tackle the problem.
</P>
<P>
The report said priority should be given to solving the
problems of water and air pollution, urban garbage and
desertification.
</P>
<P>
When the session opened this morning, Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao
delivered a report encouraging coordinated development of the
environment and the economy.
</P>
<P>
Wen, also a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China Central Committee, said the CPPCC has been
attaching great importance to the country's environmental
protection and ecological construction.
</P>
