<HEADLINE> Khatami Calls for Change in Administrative System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad Khatami
on Tuesday called for a fundamental change in the country's
administrative and managerial system.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a seminar sponsored by the Construction Jihad
Ministry, Khatami stressed that efficient decision making demands
a fundamental change in the administrative and managerial system
of the country.
</P>
<P>
Any change in the management system calls for people's
knowledge and strong will of different powers, the Islamic
Republic News Agency quoted him as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, the Iranian president gave no specific reasons for
the fundamental change in the country's administrative system.
</P>
