<HEADLINE> China Beats Russia to Enter Final Eight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 22 (Xinhua) -- China beat Russia 4-0 to enter
the quarter-finals of the World Women's Youth Softball
Championships in Taipei, China on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese women recorded four wins and one defeat in Group B
to anchor a berth in the final eight, thus a 0-1 defeat to Japan
later became meaningless.
</P>
<P>
Japan topped Group B with an unbeaten record in six outings.
Australia and Russia, who were 4-2 and 3-3 respectively, also
advanced to the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
In Group A, the United States has guarenteed a place in the
final eight along with Canada and Venezuela. The remaining place
will be decided between Chinese Taipei and New Zealand after their
match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
