<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Improves Management of Fodder Manufacturing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- China will strengthen the
management on fodder and fodder additives to ensure the healthy
development of animal husbandry.
</P>
<P>
At a news conference held here today, Qi Jingfa, vice-minister
of agriculture said that China's first related regulations came
into effect on May 29.
</P>
<P>
China is both a major fodder manufacturer and consumer with
last year's output value of the forage industry reaching 130
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
But Qi noted that some problems are hindering the healthy
development of the industry, such as the importing of below-
standard fodder.
</P>
<P>
The new regulation has outlined clearly the principle and scope
of the management methods required, said Qi.
</P>
<P>
Newly developed fodder and additives can only be made after
checks on its safety and effectiveness and no hormone medicines
are permitted to be added during manufacturing, according to the
regulations.
</P>
<P>
The regulations also called for registration of overseas fodder
and fodder additives when they are imported for the first time.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
