<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Holds Talks with WB Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
held talks Tuesday morning with visiting World Bank Managing
Director Zhang Shengman at the State House here on bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
A press release from the President's Office said the two
discussed the impact of World Bank programs and activities on
development.
</P>
<P>
Museveni said Uganda's partnership with the World Bank and the
International Monetary Fund has been useful to the development of
the economy, especially in ensuring micro-economic stability,
liberalization and the control of inflation.
</P>
<P>
The president mentioned the importance of deliberate
intervention to stimulate production. He also touched on regional
political and economic integration in solving the problem of small
markets on the continent.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank official expressed satisfaction with the
economic progress Uganda has achieved in the last 13 years and
assured the president of continued cooperation.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Uganda's Prime Minister Apollo Nsibambi also met
with the World Bank delegation which arrived in the country over
the weekend. 
</P>
</TEXT>
