<HEADLINE> Verlaat Returns to Ajax </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Dutch defender Frank Verlaat has
returned to Ajax Amsterdam from German club VfB Stuttgart on a
four-year contract, according to reports from Amsterdam,
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Verlaat, 31, has played only once for the national side but was
a member of the Dutch squad which travelled to Brazil earlier this
month.
</P>
<P>
Verlaat began his professional career at Ajax, playing for them
for three seasons before leaving for Swiss club Lausanne. He has
also played for French club Auxerre.
</P>
<P>
Verlaat is the third former Ajax player to return to the fold,
following goalkeeper Stanley Menzo and midfielder Aron Winter.
</P>
</TEXT>
