<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Australian stocks finished higher
Tuesday helped by Telstra, the biggest company in the country.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index climbed 23.1 points to
3,004.8.
</P>
<P>
The market welcomed the news that the federal government had
won senate approval to sell off a further 16.6 percent of Telstra,
a communications group, sending that stock 16 cents higher to 8.27
Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The banking index shot up 19.3 points to 6,639.1, with ANZ bank
spiking 23 cents to 11.35 Australian dollars and Westpac bank
recovering 17 cents to 9.90 Australian dollars. National Australia
Bank shed 14 cents to 25.86 Australian dollars and Commonwealth
Bank offloaded 20 cents to 24.80 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the resource sector, Rio Tinto picked up 41 cents to 24.46
Australian dollars, while BHP retreated 28 cents to 17.30
Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 442.65 million stocks traded for 749.3
million Australian dollars (489 million U.S. dollars). Rising
stocks slightly outnumbered falling stocks by 671 to 670 and 467
stocks remained steady. 
</P>
</TEXT>
