<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stock Index Surpasses 14,000-point Level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks broke through
the 14,000-point level Tuesday, the highest since October 1997,
consolidating the previous session's strong gains of 585.96 points.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index rose 10.65 points, or 0.08 percent, to
close at 14,004.88 while the market's turnover amounted to 11.699
billion HK dollars (1.5 billion U.S. dollars), slightly down from
12.09 billion HK dollars (1.55 billion U.S. dollars) Monday.
</P>
<P>
Local brokers described Tuesday's trading as "an impressive
performance," saying that the market had no difficulty digesting
the previous session's gain of 4.37 percent.
</P>
<P>
Shares for finance and utilities registered respective declines
of 1 percent and 0.44 percent and those for properties and
commerce and industry rose 1.34 percent and 1.33 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares went up sharply with the Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index climbing 4.87 percent to 562.46 points and the
Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index gaining 3.28 percent
to 1,150.54 points.
</P>
<P>
The stock market had a slight gain of 0.84 points, or 0.01
percent, to open at 13,995.07 Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
The HSI rose 38.40 points, or 0.27 percent, to end the morning
session at 14,032.63. 
</P>
</TEXT>
