<HEADLINE> S. African President to Attend Lusaka Summit on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 22 (Xinhua) -- South African President Thabo
Mbeki will lead a government delegation to Lusaka, Zambia Saturday
for a regional summit on the conflict in the Democratic Republic
of Congo (DRC), his office announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will include Foreign Minister Nkosazana Zuma,
Provincial and Local Government Minister Sydney Mufamadi, Deputy
Foreign Minister Aziz Pahad and Mbeki's senior advisers, the
office said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
This is the first foreign visit by Mbeki since his inauguration
on June 16.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki's legal advisor Mojanku Gumbi and Foreign Ministry
Director- General Jackie Selebi, together with other senior
Foreign Ministry officials left the country Tuesday morning for
preparatory talks on the DRC conflict between President Laurent
Kabila's government and Tutsi rebels. 
</P>
