<HEADLINE> China's Top Legislator Examines Law on Welfare Donations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislative body, the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC), is
examining a draft law concerning public welfare donations.
</P>
<P>
"The law aims to stimulate public welfare through boosting the
administration of procedures for pledging and receiving charity
donations," said Zhang Xuwu, vice-chairman of the NPC Law
Committee.
</P>
<P>
The draft law is among 15 bills which will be examined by the
10th Meeting of the Ninth NPC, which began here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said the revision of the draft has various options,
which, for example, called for greater concerns about handicapped
people and sports activities.
</P>
<P>
"The Law Committee has suggested that all contents concerning
the collection of donations be deleted because these activities
should come under special regulations," Zhang said.  
</P>
