<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Chairman Hails Sino-Russian Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislator Li Peng
said today that China is pleased to see that Sino-Russian exchange
and cooperation in politics, economy, culture and other areas have
been growing constantly, as the two countries have forged an equal
and mutually-trusting partnership of strategic cooperation geared
towards the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Li, chairman of the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC)
Standing Committee, made the remarks during a meeting here this
afternoon with Oleg Korolyov, vice-chairman of Russia's Federation
Council, who is here for a two day seminar on Sino-Russian
regional cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"China and Russia share a border of more than 4,000 kilometers
and the friendship between the two peoples has a long history," Li
said.
</P>
<P>
"Sino-Russian regional cooperation constitutes an important
part in the comprehensive collaboration between the two countries
and its imperative to explore ways of expanding such cooperation,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
Li briefed the Russian visitors on the NPC's operations and
said that the NPC is ready to further advance its friendly ties
with Russia's Federation Council and State Duma, to increase
mutual understanding and push forward the healthy development of
Sino-Russian relations.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed the Russian visitors on China's reform and
economic growth with the prerequisite of maintaining stability, as
well as China's independent foreign policy of peace.
</P>
<P>
Korolyov said that the Russian and Chinese peoples share a
profound friendship and the Russian people are quite moved by
China's recent grand commemoration marking the 200th anniversary
of the noted Russian poet Pushkin.
</P>
<P>
Russian parliamentarians also speak highly of China's economic
achievements over the past 50 years and appreciate China's
constructive role in handling international affairs and crises,
Korolyov told Li.  
</P>
