<HEADLINE> Iran Underlines Collective Utilization of Caspian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi underlined here on Tuesday that the resources of the
Caspian Sea should be utilized collectively for the development of
the littoral states.
</P>
<P>
"Any unilateral utilization of the Caspian resource...is not
acceptable for Iran," Kharrazi said at the opening session of the
7th International Congress on the Caucasus and Central Asia.
</P>
<P>
The minister underlined that the Caspian Sea belongs to all
the littoral states and warned that any country doing otherwise
will be fully responsible for its actions which can incur damages
on other littoral states.
</P>
<P>
He also warned against any damage to the sea's environment and
reiterated that Iran is against the plan to lay oil and gas
pipeline on the Caspian seabed, given the fact that the region is
prone to earthquakes.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi called on the littoral states not to allow foreign
forces to intervene in the region.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated Tehran's claim that Iran is the best route for
transferring the Caspian oil and gas to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day meeting, experts from 25 countries will
exchange views on issues related to the Caspian Sea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
