<HEADLINE> Earthquake Strikes Banda Aceh, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 22 (Xinhua) -- A tectonic earthquake, measuring
5.5 on the Richter scale, struck Banda Aceh municipality,
Indonesia, at 14:14 local time Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake is estimated to be located 500
kilometers southwest of Banda Aceh in the Indian Ocean, at a depth
of 33 kilometers, Antara News Agency quoted a geophysics analyst
Sugeng as saying.
</P>
<P>
Up till now, no casualty or property damage has been reported
in the Banda Aceh area, said the report.
</P>
<P>
During the past six months, Banda Aceh has been struck by
earthquakes five times.
</P>
<P>
"Aceh is vulnerable to tectonic earthquakes because it lies on
the quake line that stretches along the Bukit Barisan mountain
ranges, from Lampung to Sabang in Aceh," Sugeng said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
