<HEADLINE> Nostalgia Rules As Famous Store Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- One of China's oldest, once
biggest and most well loved commercial retail outlets is to be
reduced to rubble after sixty years in business to make way for a
modern plaza.
</P>
<P>
News of the demolition last month spread like wildfire amongst
Nanjing's population and people have flocked to the old store to
have nostalgic commemorative photographs taken or buy souvenirs.
At peak times the store was handling 400,000 customers and
visitors a day and was racking up daily sales volumes of over 10
million yuan (about 1.2 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Nanjing Central Shopping Mall was built in 1936, financed
by a group of prominent figures in the then Kuomintang government
and business circles, and only sold commodities made in China in
its early days.
</P>
<P>
And it remained as the top selling store in Jiangsu Province
throughout the development of the People's Republic of China since
1949, with its annual sales volume in recent years exceeding one
billion yuan (about 120 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The planned new shopping mall will boast 40,000 square meters
of floor space, four times more than the original, and will be
completed next year.
</P>
<P>
A grand closing ceremony was held Sunday afternoon in front of
the old shopping mall which was attended by leading officials from
the Jiangsu and Nanjing governments and representatives of all
social circles in the province and city.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
