<HEADLINE> China Opens First Nationwide On-line University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- China opened its first nationwide
on-line university today, marking the beginning of a new era for
its education system.
</P>
<P>
The Distant Learning School of Beijing University of Post and
Telecommunications (BUPT) is jointly sponsored by the university
and China Telecom.
</P>
<P>
The first year's intake of 1,000 students are from Beijing and
Tianjin cities and Guangdong, Liaoning and Fujian provinces. They
will attend real-time classroom lectures of the university through
the Internet and the ATM telecommunication network at 31 different
locations around the country. After earning adequate academic
credits through four years of study on line, they will gain an
official certificate or even a degree.
</P>
<P>
Apart from BUPT, Qinghua University, Hunan University and
Zhejiang University have also been given government approval to
run on-line education courses on a trial basis. However, Hunan and
Zhejiang universities are only open to on-line students in their
own provinces.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Minister of Information Industry Qu Weizhi said at the
today's ceremony that on-line distant learning will lead to a
revolution in the means of education in China. She said that it is
a major step forward in the drive to rejuvenate the nation through
scientific and technological advances and a vital way to improve
national competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
Zuo Feng, director of the Data Communications Bureau of China
Telecom, noted that limited resources have restricted further
expansion of the higher education market in China. He said that on-
line education will make full use of the existing educational
facilities by breaking down the barriers of time and distance. It
will help stimulate demand in a huge potential market.
</P>
<P>
China now has some 696 million employed persons. If only a
quarter of them receive further education every year, the
potential market will be 174 million persons. As a result, Qu said
that on-line education has tremendous prospects.
</P>
<P>
A student from Liaoning Province in northeast China said at the
launch ceremony that the on-line university will allow greater
flexibility for him to balance study, work and family. He said
that on-line education is the best choice for him to complete
higher education.
</P>
<P>
Noting that on-line distant learning is still in a trial stage
at present, Zuo said that the new method of education has yet to
resolve such problems as inadequate utilization of network
resources and returns of investment.
</P>
<P>
China Telecom has invested near 50 million yuan in the first
phase of setting up the Distant Learning School at BUPT. A BUPT
official said that the university is still waiting for government
approval on the level of tuition fees of on-line education.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the first year of on-line students are
employees from post and telecommunications bureaus in various
localities. The university is yet to get government approval to
widen the base of students to people from all trades, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
