<HEADLINE> 9 Killed, 80 Injured in India's Bomb Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 22 (Xinhua) -- At least nine people were killed
and 80 others injured in a powerful bomb explosion at new
Jalpaiguri railway station about 1,500 kilometers west of New
Delhi Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that two of 12 Indian soldiers bound
for the Kargil battle front in Kashmir were among those killed in
the blast.
</P>
<P>
The condition of 42 of the injured was "critical" and some of
them died in hospital.
</P>
<P>
The blast area has been cordoned off and the cause of the blast
is not clear yet. 
</P>
