Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- The Kosovo Liberation Army (KLA) has ordered its fighters to
surrender their heavy weapons within 90 days. The spokesman of the
U.S. State Department said that the unilateral commitment by the
KLA will allow it to play a "determining role" in the
reconstruction of the administration of the province.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The French company Thomson SCF-RCM has been ordered to pay
100,000 francs (about 16,000 U.S. dollars) in fines by a court in
Versailles for violating the law on 35-hour work a week. The court
made the verdict that the company's managing staff worked more
than 35 hours a week.
</P>
<P>
-- While an international aid for the reconstruction of Kosovo
began to be established, U.S. President Bill Clinton and German
Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder announced on Tuesday in Bonn that a
conference on a stability pact in the Balkans will be held in July
in Sarajevo. 
</P>
