<HEADLINE> FM Spokeswoman on Kosovo Peace-keeping Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- China today urged all parties to
abide by principles of the U.N. Charter as well as to respect
national sovereignty of Yugoslavia in their peace-keeping efforts
in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Not only international security presence but also civilian
presence led by the United Nations or other organizations must
maintain just, neutral and objective position on the issue,
Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue said.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with U.N. Security Council Resolution 1244, the
international security and civilian presence in Kosovo should be
deployed in the name of the United Nations, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
 
</P>
