<HEADLINE> China Confers Award on Canadian Expert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Science and
Technology today conferred an International Scientific and
Technological Cooperation Award on Jean Sabourin, an expert with
the Canadian International Development Program (CIDP).
</P>
<P>
"Mr. Sabourin has contributed a lot to CIDP's aid program in
China, concerning Sino-Canadian cooperation in electricity, oil
and gas, digital communications and other areas," said Hui
Yongzheng, Vice-Minister of Science and Technology at today's
conferring ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Sabourin, who is also a senior expert in energy, has also paid
great attention to the cultivation of talents, Hui said. Under his
coordination more than 200 Chinese engineers have been to Canada
to receive technical training, and a series of training classes
have also been held in China by Canadian experts.
</P>
<P>
Established by the State Council in 1995, the International
Scientific and Technological Cooperation Award rewards
international scientists and experts who have made important
contribution to promoting scientific cooperation between China and
the rest of the world. So far 14 foreign experts have won the
award.  
</P>
</TEXT>
