<HEADLINE> FM Spokeswoman on North-South Korean Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- China hopes that progress would be
made in the current Vice-ministerial talks between North and South
Korea in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
"China welcomes the talks," said Zhang Qiyue, Chinese Foreign
Ministry spokeswoman here this afternoon at a regular press
conference. "China will continue to play a positive role in
maintaining the relaxation and stability on the Korean Peninsular.
"
</P>
<P>
The Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) and the
Republic of Korea (ROK) began talks here this morning.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said China always holds that DPRK and ROK should solve
their problems through dialogue and consultation.
</P>
<P>
China had been informed before the talks by relevant parties
that the talks will focus on the reunion of separated families in
the two parts of the Korean Peninsula and other issues with common
concern, she said.
</P>
<P>
A fundamental principle China sticks to on the Korean Peninsula
issue is to maintain peace and stability of the region, Zhang said,
adding that to this end, China has offered the conference venue
for talks between North and South Korea, as well as between DPRK
and the United States.
</P>
<P>
DPRK and the United States are expected to hold talks in
Beijing tomorrow. 
</P>
</TEXT>
