<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientist Develops Way To Keep Paper Money Cleaner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, June 22 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese scientist has developed
a disinfectant that can kill 99.9 percent of harmful bacteria on
bank notes and keep them clean for four years.
</P>
<P>
Wang Xueping, a chemist with the Science Commission of China's
Shanxi Province, the developer of the disinfectant, says that the
soaking treatment method and its effectiveness has been confirmed
by a panel of specialists in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Wang says that it can also be used to sanitize towels, clothing
and telephone sets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
