<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top Legislature Deliberates on Three International Treaties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Three international treaties on
judicial cooperation between China and Viet Nam, the Republic of
Korea and Ukraine were submitted to China's top legislature for
deliberation today.
</P>
<P>
The 9th National People's Congress Standing Committee convened
its 10th meeting this morning.
</P>
<P>
The three treaties include one with Viet Nam on judicial
assistance in civil and criminal cases, one with the Republic of
Korea on judicial assistance in criminal cases, and an extradition
treaty with the Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
They were signed in Beijing in October, November and December
of 1998 respectively.
</P>
<P>
In explaining the treaties on behalf of the State Council, Vice
Foreign Minister Yang Jiechi told legislators that the State
Council, after examination, held that the content of three
treaties tallies with Chinese laws, the country's juridical
practices and internationally-accepted practices.
</P>
<P>
He said that the firming up of the three treaties will be
conducive to China's cooperation with the three countries in the
judicial field, and to the further development of bilateral
relations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990622.0153 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
