<HEADLINE> Air France to Set up Alliance with U.S. Delta Airlines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 22 (Xinhua) -- France's national carrier Air France
said Tuesday that it intends to establish a strategic partnership
with the U.S. Delta Airlines.
</P>
<P>
The Executive Officer of Air France Jean Cyril Spinetta has
presented its administration council a project of agreement with
the Delta Airlines, said Air France, a 100 percent state-owned
company until one year ago.
</P>
<P>
Spinetta is expected to announce the company's decision to set
up a "strategic alliance" with the Atlanta-based Delta Airlines
later Tuesday at a press conference.
</P>
<P>
He said recently that Air France plans to expand into a global
air company by setting up alliance with other air companies.
</P>
<P>
Delta Airlines made a profit of 1.08 billion U.S. dollars and
realized a sales figure of 14.4 billion dollars in 1998 while Air
France made a profit of 257 million dollars and had a sales figure
of 9.4 billion dollars last year. 
</P>
