<HEADLINE> China's Steel Empire Introduces Environmental Protection Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The city of Anshan in
northeastern China has the country's biggest steel producer and
has decided to clean up its smoke-blackened sky.
</P>
<P>
The face-lift includes importing production lines from Italy
and technology from the United States to cut pollution.
</P>
<P>
The Anshan Steel Corporation was the first steel producer of
the People's Republic and is still the nation's pride because it
provided the steel for the country's automobiles, airplanes and
satellites.
</P>
<P>
But, since the 1980s, the plant, which employs 300,000 people,
has become one of the country's biggest sources of sulfur dioxide
and dust in the air.
</P>
<P>
Wu Yesong, deputy mayor of Anshan, has announced that the city
recently established an environmental engineering corporation to
handle people's complaints and it and other companies will develop
technology to deal with the problem and produce equipment for cars
using newer fuel sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
