<HEADLINE> Foreign Investors Benefit From Service Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 22 (Xinhua) -- A foreign investment service
center in the northern Chinese port city of Tianjin has helped
increase of city's foreign funds in its 12 years of existence.
</P>
<P>
There were only 226 foreign-funded enterprises, worth less than
30 million U.S. dollars, before 1978, but today the number has
risen to more than 12,000, worth 24 billion U.S. dollars, 208 of
them multinationals, making Tianjin the city with the most foreign
investment in northern China.
</P>
<P>
The increase has resulted from the efforts of the service
center, officials say. It mainly provides registration services
and consultation, providing convenience for foreign business
people.
</P>
<P>
Albert Yeung, general manager of Smith Kline &AMP; French, says
that the service center has solved investment procedure problems,
and Ji Zhongqiang, deputy general manager of Korea's LG, calls it
the "home of foreign-funded enterprises". It has helped Japan's
Mitsumi Electric smoothly increase its capital from 10 million U.S.
dollars to 70 million, according to the general manager, Tadshi
Tamura.
</P>
<P>
However, Pi Qiansheng, the center's director, says that they
still have a lot to do in improving service to keep management
costs down and the city has rescinded over 500 different fees for
foreign-funded enterprises this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
