<HEADLINE> Mozambique in Need of 325,000 Tons of Food in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique is estimated to be in
need of about 325,000 tons of food in the 1999/2000 financial year
(starting from July to next June).
</P>
<P>
This was revealed here Monday by Jose Egidio Paulo, director of
the National Commerce Bureau, the Noticias newspaper reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
So far, rice production in Mozambique is only 116,000 tons, as
against its yearly consumption of 250,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, he said, the country needs to import 60,000 tons of
maize, 175,000 tons of wheat and 150,000 tons of rice in the
coming fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Fortunately, he added, the production of cassava, sorghum and
millet are sufficient for domestic consumption.
</P>
<P>
The government will resort to border trade to solve the
problem, he said.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
