<DOCNO> XIE19990622.0174 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Revise Marine Environment Protection Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislature has
decided to revise the country's Marine Environment Protection Law,
the first time in 16 years, in a bid to improve the protection of
marine resources and maintain a ecological balance.
</P>
<P>
This was announced today by Zhang Haoruo, vice-chairman of the
Committee of Environment and Resources Protection of the National
People's Congress, in his explanation to the tenth meeting of the
National People's Congress Standing Committee on the draft of the
revised law.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that marine environmental disasters such as red tide
and the pollution of seawater aquatics have increased because of
the large amounts of urban sewage discharges and the discharge of
industrial and agricultural waste water into the sea. The current
regulations are unable to prevent the worsening situation in this
regard, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The draft of the revised law has thus added such amendments as
marine environment supervision and management, marine ecological
protection, the prevention of land pollutants to marine
environment and the prevention of coastal and marine construction
projects to marine environment, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
The present law, which was promulgated at the beginning of the
reform and opening-up in the early 1980s, focuses on controlling
oceanic pollution and cannot be adapted to meet the needs of the
country's sustainable development strategy.
</P>
<P>
"It also has loopholes concerning the overall monitoring and
management of the marine environment, thus needing amendment,"
Zhang stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990622.0175 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yangjin, First Female Lawyer in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Among 53 professional lawyers in
10 lawyer's offices in Tibet, Yangjin is well known not just
because she is a woman, but also for her cooperative lawyer's
office launched in 1993, the first of its kind in the Tibet
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
So far, Yangjin has handled some 800 legal cases, and served as
lawyer for over 100 enterprises. She helped recoup some 70 million
yuan for them.
</P>
<P>
She worked as the defending lawyer for 310 criminal cases and
had the suspects in 41 of the cases released free.
</P>
<P>
For years, the fully-occupied Yangjin has never known weekends
as she has to be present on the court four or even five times a
week.
</P>
<P>
"I am busy because the Tibetans have gained legal knowledge,"
said Yangjin, adding, "They realize the importance of living on
law. This is why there are so many enterprises and companies that
employ their own attorneys."
</P>
<P>
"In the past, the Tibetans felt insulted to go to court. They
prefer to have a senior villager to help solve any disputes. Our
business means the progress of the society," she said.
</P>
<P>
Whenever entrusted with an economic case, Yangjin plunged into
work right away. Once, a construction company boss used up his
money for an economic case. He borrowed 2,000 yuan from Yangjin
and promised to pay her back soon. But he never did so.
</P>
<P>
"When I worked for others, I do my best to win for them," said
Yangjin. "So far as I am concerned, I don't know how to get back
my money."
</P>
<P>
Outside the court. Yangjin is somewhat shy. She speaks slowly
and in a tender voice. Given her success, Yangjin, 35 this year,
is one of Top 10 Lawyers in China and one of Top 10 Youths in
China.
</P>
<P>
In 1985, Yangjin, then 21, graduated form the Southwest
Political and Legal Institute and was assigned to work in the
Legal Commission of the Tibet Autonomous Regional Government.
</P>
<P>
It was an office of six lawyers and Yangjin turned out to be
the only female among them.
</P>
<P>
Four years later, Yangjin opened her own economic attorney
office, which was the first of its kind in Tibet. In 1993, she
launched Tibet's first cooperative lawyer's office.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
