<HEADLINE> 10th Meeting of 9th NPC Standing Committee Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The 10th meeting of the 9th
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, which began
today, will deliberate on 15 bills of draft laws and resolutions.
</P>
<P>
This meeting has the largest number of bills to be discussed
since the current NPC Standing Committee started work in March
last year.
</P>
<P>
The meeting today heard reports on the deliberation of the
draft law for the prevention of crimes committed by minors, the
draft garrison law for the Macao Special Administrative Region,
and the draft law on donation to public welfare projects.
</P>
<P>
The three draft laws are expected to be passed during the
current meeting.
</P>
<P>
Committee members also heard clarifications of the draft
explanations on Clause 22, Article 4, and Clause 24, Article 2,
Item 3 of the Basic Law for the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region, made by the Commission of Legislative Affairs of the NPC
Standing Committee, and deliberated on the State Council's motion
on the deliberation and explanation of the above mentioned
provisions.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also heard reports on the revision of the draft
laws for national high and new technology development zones,
solely individual-invested enterprises, as well as explanations on
the revised draft law on the protection of the ocean environment
and the draft law on the management and utilization of
meteorological resources.
</P>
<P>
It also heard explanations about the revised draft law for
accounting, draft resolutions on the punishment of crimes against
the accounting law and punishment of crimes in futures trading,
and explanations on three bills concerning international treaties.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will also hear and deliberate on reports of the
final state accounts for 1998 and the implementation of the 1998
budget made by the Finance Ministry and the National Audit Office
respectively, that on the inspection of the implementation of the
law for air pollution prevention and control by the NPC Standing
Committee, that on air pollution prevention and control in Beijing
by the State Environmental Protection Administration, and a
written report on the overseas visits by NPC delegations.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee, presided over the
opening ceremony this morning.  
</P>
</TEXT>
