<HEADLINE> East China Firm Raises Capital on Shenzhen Bourse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The Fengyuan Biochemical Co. Ltd.
of east China's Anhui Province raised 375.6 million yuan from the
initial public offering (IPO) of shares on the Shenzhen Stock
Exchange Monday.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the company said it sold 60 million A shares at a
price of 6.5 yuan per share yesterday. The move was designed to
raise funds to expand the company's citric acid production and
export capacity.
</P>
<P>
The east China company has a 25 percent share of the domestic
citric acid market and ten percent of the international market. It
is the largest maker of citric acid and other related products in
Asia.
</P>
<P>
The corporate sources said that a half of the raised funds
would be used to introduce new technology for producing citric
acid directly from fermented corn flour. The company is now able
to produce 50,000 tons of citric acid annually and is hoping to
boost that to 100,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Citric acid is an organic acid that can be used for many things
including the making of food-stuffs, beverages, pharmaceuticals
and detergents.
</P>
<P>
By late next year, the company will increase its citric acid
exports to 90,000 tons. By then, it will also have a 17 percent
share of the international market, said the sources. 
</P>
