<HEADLINE> Books on Ancient Egypt Selling Well in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Books on ancient Egypt are
selling like hot cakes here, at the same time as an Egyptian
relics exhibition has been attracting over 10,000 visitors every
day.
</P>
<P>
The two-month exhibition of more than 100 invaluable Egyptian
relics normally housed in the British Museum opened here last
Friday and is luring a record number of visitors from the city and
neighboring Jiangsu and Zhejiang provinces to the Shanghai Museum.
</P>
<P>
Photo albums related to the exhibition are being snapped up by
visitors, despite their prices being several times higher than
those of the tickets to the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
`Unveiling the Mysteries of Ancient Egypt", a translated
pamphlet published by the Shanghai Bookstore Publishing House, is
being reprinted only six months after it first appeared.
</P>
<P>
Another book, Travels in Egypt, written by two Chinese scholars
who worked in Egypt for over four years, is also selling well.
