<HEADLINE> Sino-U.S. Cooperation to Develop Wind Power </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The Tang Energy Group Ltd. of the
United States recently signed a contract with China's Xinjiang
Wind Power Corporation to develop wind power in the western part
of China.
</P>
<P>
The two firms will spend 200 million yuan increasing the wind
power output at Dabancheng from 12,000 kw. to 22,800 kw.
</P>
<P>
The Tang Energy Group holds 70 percent of the 76 million yuan
in registered capital and the Xinjiang firm is providing
technology and generators. The project is expected to begin
operation within 2 years.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang has 9 wind power zones on a 150,000-sq.km. area with
800 billion kwh. of power reserves.
</P>
<P>
Patrick Jenevein, chairman of the Tang Energy Group, says that
the business and economic cooperation will benefit both sides and
Yu Wuming, a senior engineer at Xinjiang Wind Power, says that the
project will increase the wind power capacity in Xinjiang, cut
environmental pollution, and promote the development of other
industries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
