<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Launch Tourist Promotion in Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka will launch a massive
tourist promotion roadshow in Germany next month in a up-market
drive to boost tourist arrivals, Tourist Board sources said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The roadshow will be sponsored jointly by Sri Lanka's Tourist
Board and the national carrier Air Lanka, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Germany is Sri Lanka's largest tourist market with 27,126
arrivals during the first quarter of 1999. Last year tourist
arrivals from Germany was 74,058.
</P>
<P>
The roadshow by boat titled "Sunny Island Ship" will sail
through 25 German cities on a converted container ship.
</P>
<P>
The ship will set off from Berlin in early July and moor in
Frankfurt in August in time for the famous "Museumsuferfest", a
popular festival by the river Main. The journey will end on
September 22 in Stuttgart.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the roadshow will take the form of a travel
fair on the move and the theme selected is to present the most
beautiful island and coastal areas in the world.
</P>
<P>
The Tourist Board expects the roadshow will improve and
strengthen Sri Lanka's image as a sunny and enchanting island
destination for tourists offering numerous attractions and
facilities.
</P>
<P>
The board expects a 17 percent rise in tourist arrivals this
year to around 446,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
