<HEADLINE> Ecuador's Foreign Ministry to Cut Overhead Costs Amid Financial Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Economic crisis has made Ecuador's
Foreign Ministry look for new ways to reduce its overhead costs,
local press said Monday.
</P>
<P>
One of the measures was to close down Ecuador's diplomatic
missions in foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of this year, three consulates and an
embassy have been closed. The consulate in Philadelphia and the
Embassy in Romania were closed in March, and the consulates in
Hong Kong, China, and Valparaiso, Chile suspended their business a
few days ago.
</P>
<P>
In the case of Philadelphia, it is believed that the work of
the consulate there can be transferred to New Jersey or New York.
</P>
<P>
The problems of the Foreign Ministry were basically caused by
its cut in budget and the delay in the payment of its allowance by
the Finance Ministry.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, its operating costs were around 24 million dollars,
and the figure is expected to be around 27 million dollars this
year.
</P>
<P>
Due to a government cut in the budget, the Foreign Ministry
will only receive 21 million dollars this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
