<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The number of foreign
tourists visiting Argentina increased from two million in 1990 to
more than three million in 1998, up 54 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest report from Argentina's Economy
Ministry, the amount of foreign currency brought into the country
by the visitors reached 3.2 billion dollars in 1998, increasing
more than 183 percent compared to 1.13 billion in 1990.
</P>
<P>
