<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Mongolian President Nachagyn
Bagbandy said on Monday that his country badly needs foreign aid
and loans to help tide over the country's economic difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening of a two-day international conference
on economic aid to Mongolia, Bagbandy said the government will
take measures like financial reform, privatization of big
enterprises and development of infrastructure to check the
economic problem, but this goal can not be achieved by only
relying on the country's own financial resources.
</P>
