<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Carry Out National Food Hygiene Campaign in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The Food Administration Department
of Vietnam will carry out a nation-wide food hygiene, quality and
safety campaign throughout the month of July, said Vietnam News on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Food Administration Department of the Ministry of Health
will work with Vietnam's related ministries and branches to
mobilize the mass media to raise public awareness of food
poisoning prevention and preparation of healthy and safe meals.
</P>
<P>
The campaign will take the safety of imported goods into
account.
</P>
<P>
In the Ho Chi Minh City food markets, powdered milk made by
European companies, which lately have been embroiled in a scandal
over contamination with the carcinogenic substance dioxin, was
still being displayed and sold as usual.
</P>
<P>
Imported European milk products account for 30 percent of the
milk products displayed and sold in Ho Chi Minh City. These milk
products have not been tested for quality, hygiene or safety
because such tests are very expensive, said local authorities,
adding that in addition, the test results may not be totally
accurate because of the backward state of the local testing
center.
</P>
<P>
The campaign will also concentrate on small-scale food
production enterprises, private food and beverage manufacturing
businesses and popular restaurants where hygiene and safety
standards are not observed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
