<P>
This was disclosed at a meeting between Sri Lankan Trade
Minister Kingsley T. Wickremeratne and Austrian Ambassador Herbert
Traxl here Monday, the official sources said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
They discussed a range of concerns pertaining to further
improving Austrian trade and investments in Sri Lanka, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed to consider a proposal to set up a Sri
Lanka-Austria Business Council following their discussions.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka's main exports to Austria are garments, tea, tobacco,
coconut and leather products.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan trade minister asked Austria to encourage medium
and small investors and trading agents to locate their business in
Sri Lanka by using the advantage of the existing trade network.
</P>
<P>
He also explained that new opportunities in industries,
engineering and rubber molds are also available for potential
Austrian investors, the sources added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
