<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian Tennis Association
(Pelti) is preparing to select a coach to train the men's team for
the 20th Southeast Asian (SEA) Games, the Jakarta Post reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Pelti spokesman Benny Mailili said the association would choose
the coach from 15 people invited to a one-day discussion on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Those invited include Tintus Aribowo, former national coach who
trained the Davis Cup team, Deddy Prasetyo, current coach for
former Davis Cup players being groomed for the SEA Games,
Suharyadi, current coach for the women's national team and Yayuk
Basuki, a retired woman player.
</P>
