he is recognized by the players," Benny said.
</P>
<P>
Benny said the eight players (four men and four women) who will
participate in the SEA Games will be chosen through a national
selection. The selection period for the men will be from June 23
to 26, while the women will be selected from July 1 to 3.
</P>
<P>
Wynne Prakusya, ranked 190th in the world, has been given an
automatic berth on the SEA Games women's team.
</P>
<P>
"National selection must go on despite the funding crisis.
Each participant, whether they win or lose, will get a performance
fee," Benny added. 
