<HEADLINE> Panama to Construct Largest Trade Center in C.A. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Panama is constructing one of
the largest and most modern trade centers of the Central America
and Caribbean on the old site of the North American air-base,
Albrook, the Inter-Oceanic Regional Authority (ARI) said Monday.
</P>
<P>
ARI, an official autonomous entity in charge of the
administration of U.S.-returned properties, said that this mega-
project, named Albrook People's Trade Center, has involved various
domestic and foreign companies, which have invested more than 100
million U.S. dollars in total.
</P>
<P>
Investors of the center, to be built on a 60-hectare site, can
lease for forty years, during which the Panamanian state will
receive tax payments.
</P>
<P>
According to ARI, the trade project, located just a few
kilometers from the city limits of the Panamanian capital, will
help the local population to get supply merchandise and healthy
diversion.
</P>
<P>
The project is just one of a dozen development plans of the
Panamanian government in the zone of the inter-oceanic canal which
was returned to Panama in the last three years.
</P>
<P>
Another mega-project, competing with Albrook, is the Tourist
Center of Amador, a modern tourist installation invested by Korean,
Spanish, Canadian and American businessmen.
</P>
<P>
Amador, on the Pacific coast and about 30-minute drive from the
Panamanian capital, is to become a large tourist resort with three
islands connected by pedestrian walkways. 
</P>
</TEXT>
