<HEADLINE> Volunteers Secure Blood Supply for Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- While hospitals in many Chinese
cities are facing a severe shortage of blood, local volunteers in
this southwest China municipality have secured the supply needed
by local hospitals.
</P>
<P>
The majority of Chongqing's population live in the countryside,
and many rural residents had never heard of blood donation until
last October. But since then over 8.8 million ml of blood have
been donated by the volunteers.
</P>
<P>
The city issued its own regulations on blood donation
immediately after a related state law went into effect last
October. Under the local rules, the volunteers are given a certain
subsidy, and are guaranteed blood free of charge when they
themselves are in need.
</P>
<P>
The municipal blood-collection center has sent vehicles to
patrol the streets soliciting donations.  
</P>
