<HEADLINE> System For Assessing Human Resources In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 22 (Xinhua) -- A new scientific system of
assessing human resources is gaining popularity at Chinese
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
It appraises people's comprehensive ability and is expected to
rule out subjective factors in recruiting workers. It is already
being used in the cities of Beijing, Shanghai, and Tianjin and the
southern province of Guangdong. The first such assessment agency
in Tianjin, the Human Resources Assessment Co. Ltd., has helped
more than 40 enterprises assess 2,500 personnel.
</P>
<P>
It took Chinese specialists three years to develop the system,
which is based on data from more than 3,600 management personnel
across the country.
</P>
<P>
The newly emerging business of quality assessment is a result
of the introduction of the market economy, which allows
enterprises to recruit on their own people instead of just
accepting whoever the government assigns to them, one Ministry of
Personnel official explains.
</P>
<P>
However, he also points out that the business is still new and
that there are many improvements needed to better assess human
resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
