<HEADLINE> City Of Tianjin Has 460 Trees More Than 300 Years Old </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The northern Chinese city of
Tianjin has found 461 trees more than 300 years old, 8 of which
are more than 1,000 years old.
</P>
<P>
They were discovered during a recent activity to select "King
Tree". The honor went to 3 of the trees that are more than 1,000
years old.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese pine accounts for the greatest number of old trees,
followed by the Japanese Pagoda tree, and oriental arborvitae.
Most of the trees were found in the northern suburbs on hills that
have rich soil.
</P>
<P>
The trees are regarded as living antiques and provide important
information about the city's history and local folklore, according
to one folklorist and they also show that the city has made an
effort to protect things of historical interest.
</P>
<P>
To better protect these old trees, the city has a project for
encouraging citizens to sponsor a specific tree or grassy area.
</P>
