<HEADLINE> Trainer Plane Crashes in Poland, Injuring Four </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, June 21 (Xinhua) -- A Polish French-made TR-20 trainer
plane Sunday crashed near Rylina in the northern mountainous area
of Slovakia, injuring all the four pilots -- two Poles and two
Slovaks -- on board, with one Polish pilot in critical condition.
</P>
<P>
The Polish News Agency reported that the accident occurred at
10:00 a.m. on Monday, but the Pilot Training Center of the Polish
Rzeszow Engineering Institute confirmed it only on Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
The first secretary in the Polish embassy in Slovakia said that
the cause of the accident remained unclear and a special
commission was sent to the spot for investigation.
</P>
<P>
The report said that one of the two Polish pilots, who were
invited to the Rylina Pilots' School, was in his forties and had
thousands' of hours of flying experience. The other was 26 years
old and most severely injured in the crash.
</P>
<P>
The TR-20 aircraft, a single-motor trainer, is fit to fly under
adverse conditions. It can accommodate five people in addition to
two crew members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
