<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Sports Official Jailed for Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Dietbert Friedberg, a former East
German sports official, was sentenced to six months by a Berlin
court on Monday after being found guilty of doping and causing
bodily harm to athletes in the 1970s and 1980s.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time that any sports official was sentenced to
prison in connection with the systematic doping in former East
Germany.
</P>
<P>
However, the 56-year-old physician acquired probation
automatically because the sentence was under two years and the man
has no previous convictions.
</P>
<P>
The court found Friedberg guilty of providing anabolic steroids
to athletes and swimmers in East Germany between 1977 and 1984 as
20 former East Germans filed charges against him.
</P>
<P>
The physician was the deputy director of the Sport Medical
Service of East Germany. 
</P>
</TEXT>
