<HEADLINE> China To Host Int'l Symposium On Community Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- An international symposium on
community service and development has been scheduled for June 26-
28 in this capital of east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first activity of its kind in the country.
</P>
<P>
Experts and scholars from a dozen countries and regions, such
as Canada, the United States, Japan, the Republic of Korea,
Denmark and Australia will attend the symposium. Chinese officials
and scholars from across the country, including those from Taiwan
and Hong Kong, will participate in the discussion.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu's experience in community service will be held up as an
example for the comparison between Chinese community service and
that practised overseas.
</P>
<P>
The trends in community service towards the 21st century will
also be a topic of discussion.  
</P>
</TEXT>
