<DOCNO> XIE19990622.0280 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Earthquake Measuring 5.8 Hits Central Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 21 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.8 on
the Richter scale rocked the capital city of Mexico and Puebla in
central Mexico on Monday, but there have been no reports of
casualties or structural damage.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake struck at 12:43 local time and lasted for 40
seconds, with its epicenter being between the states of Guerrerro
and Oaxaca, said the National Seismological Service.
</P>
<P>
In the capital, many people rushed out from their workplaces or
residences, but in Puebla the tremor was only felt slightly.
</P>
<P>
Last Tuesday, an earthquake measuring 6.7 on the Richter scale
hit Mexico City and the states of Oaxaca and Puebla, leaving at
least 18 people dead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
