<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0030, June 22 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The U.N. Security Council Monday expressed
concern over the situation in Congo (K) and expressed the hope to
see a successful outcome of the peace talks, scheduled for June 26
in the Zambian capital of Lusanka.
</P>
<P>
In a brief statement read to the press, the president of the
Security Council, Ismaila Jane of Gambia, said, "The members of
the Security Council expressed concern over the situation there
and expressed the hope for a successful outcome" of the planned
peace talks. (UN-Congo(K))
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkish Foreign Ministry said in a statement Monday
that the acknowledgment of the existence of "Turkish Republic of
Northern Cyprus" is the only way to the resumption of bilateral
talks in the long-divided Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
The ministry issued the statement in response to Sunday's call
of the G-8 summit for the resumption of talks in Cyprus with no
preconditions in the upcoming autumn. (Turkey-Cyprus)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MAPUTO -- Mozambican Environment Minister Bernardo Ferraz
Monday urged to avoid clashes over the management, utilization and
development of the natural resources shared by the African
countries.
</P>
<P>
Ferraz made the call at a regional workshop on African natural
resources in Mozambican capital Maputo, the Mozambican News Agency
reported. (Mozambique-African Resources)
