<HEADLINE> Deschamps to Join Chelsea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 21 (Xinhua) -- French World Cup-winning captain
Didier Deschamps agreed to a three-year deal with English Premier
League soccer club Chelsea on Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to local reports, Deschamps moved from Juventus to
join Chelsea at a transfer fee of three million pounds (about 4.77
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The midfielder finalised negotiations with the premier league
club's chief executive Colin Hutchinson who is on holiday in
Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Deschamps is a former teammate of Chelsea coach Gianluca Vialli.
The pair helped Juventus lift the European Cup in 1996.
</P>
<P>
He won the French championship twice and the European Cup at
Marseille before joining Juventus in 1994. He helped Juventus
complete the Italian league and cup double the following year.
</P>
<P>
Deschamps also played a major role in helping Juventus win the
Italian title in 1997 and 1998 and took them to the Champions
League final last year where they were beaten by Real Madrid.
</P>
<P>
Deschamps's best friend, fellow French World Cup winner Marcel
Desailly, joined Chelsea last season and recently pledged his
future to the London club. 
</P>
</TEXT>
