<HEADLINE> Dow Falls On Wall Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial average
Moved lower Monday on profit-taking from last week's gains.
</P>
<P>
The Dow closed 39.58 lower at 10,815.98. The index gained
365.05 points in the five straight sessions last week.
</P>
<P>
But the technology heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 66.84 or
2.6 percent at 2,630.28. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index rose 6.16
at 1,349.00.
</P>
<P>
The technology stocks became more attractive after the Federal
Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan indicated last week that the
Federal Reserve would raise interest rates but the rise would not
be too drastic, getting investors eased about higher interest
rates. Among leading technology stock names, Dell Computer,
Microsoft, Cisco Systems and Intel rallied as the four most active
Nasdaq issues.
</P>
<P>
Technology stocks such as Dell Computer and America Online were
down more than 30 percent from their highs in recent weeks.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index rose 0.39 at 636.94 and the American
Stock Exchange index fell 2.82 at 765.75. The Russell 2000 index
of smaller companies rose 4.39 at 449.44.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a small margin on the
New York Stock Exchange, with 1,599 up, 1,420 down and 539
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 676.12 million shares from 902 million
in the previous session. 
