<HEADLINE> Europe's Main Markets Stride to Strong Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON June 21 (Xinhua) - European stocks held most of their
strong gains Monday after a series of rallies underpinned by
strong overnight performances in Asian markets.
</P>
<P>
The UK blue chip index finished 53.4 points or 0.82 percent up
at 6581.26, within a whisker of its all-time closing high of
6598.8, set on April 28.
</P>
<P>
British Telecom jumped 5 percent, on its own contributing some
18 points to the index. HSBC was another notable gainer, up 2.7
percent after a 4.4 percent surge for the Hang Seng index
overnight.
</P>
<P>
Sharp gains on leading Asian markets together with a 2.5
percent rally in Frankfurt also helped steer the FTSE higher form
the outset.
</P>
<P>
"The rise in Hongkong and Germany is fuelled by hopes of a
synchronised global economic recovery, while the likely hike in US
rates at the end of the month has been priced in," said Jeremy
Batstone, head of research at NatWest Stockbrokers.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, the electronic Xetra Dax retreated slightly from
an early surge that drove its blue chips up nearly 3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The index ended 2.46 percent higher, at 5468.47 amid sharp
gains in chemical stocks and a surge in Japan's Nikkei index
Monday to its highest level in 20 months.
</P>
<P>
Paris' CAC 40 index ended up 0.12 percent at 4545.09, having
hit an earlier high of 4587.90 - its fourth closing record in a
row - on the back of strong Asian markets. 
