<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Urges to Protect Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
has urged people in the southwestern district of Mbarara to
protect environment by planting more trees on hill tops.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a public rally in the district Monday afternoon, the
 president said the district had been hit by an unusually
prolonged drought, a press release from the President's Office
said.
</P>
<P>
He was responding to the concern expressed by the people of the
district through their leaders to the effect that the current
drought in the area has forced some people to move to neighboring
districts and to Tanzania in search of water.
</P>
<P>
He urged local people to take the issue of environment
protection very seriously and to completely desist from
cultivating in wetlands.
</P>
<P>
The president also encouraged people of his hometown to
increase homestead incomes so as to banish poverty.
</P>
<P>
Mbarara is known for milk production. It provides milk for
most of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
