the powerful religious party won 17 seats in the May elections and
became the third-largest party in the Knesset (parliament).
</P>
<P>
But Yisrael Baaliya Party, which represents the interests of
the Russian immigrants, has accused Shas of blocking the
immigration from Russia and wants to control the ministry itself.
</P>
<P>
Yisrael Baaliya got six seats in the elections, and was Barak's
first choice to be a member of his coalition government.
</P>
<P>
Yisrael Baliya leader Natan Sharansky threatened to walk out
of the coalition should Shas be offered the ministry.
</P>
<P>
Senior sources in the One Israel coalition led by Barak have
said that a compromise could be reached between Shas and Yisrael
Baaliya over the issue.
</P>
<P>
They said that as long as Shas does not hold on to the
Interior Ministry, Sharansky will agree to give it up and take
the Housing Ministry instead. 
