<HEADLINE> SADC Peace-keeping Training Center Opens in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The Southern African Development
Community (SADC) Regional Peace-keeping Training Center officially
opened at the Zimbabwean army headquarters in Harare Monday.
</P>
<P>
The first U.N.-sponsored senior management course from Monday
to Friday is being attended by 53 officers from the region.
</P>
<P>
There is need for mutual support from SADC leaders if
peace-keeping missions are to succeed in the region, U.N.
Undersecretary-General for peace-keeping operations, Bernad Miyet,
said in a speech read on his behalf by his representative at the
opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Miyet said that peace-keeping requires specialized training,
adding that the U.N. would cooperate with the center to ensure
that it realizes its goals.
</P>
<P>
He said the center would contribute immensely in improving
cooperation in peace-keeping between the U.N., the Organization of
African Unity (OAU) and the SADC.
</P>
<P>
"The U.N. welcomes the establishment of the center. Young men
and women will come to this center to be groomed as competent and
resourceful peace- keepers in the multiple dimensions that
comprise today's peace-keeping," he said.
</P>
<P>
Miyet said peace-keeping has become complex and
multi-dimensional in nature and the U.N. depends on member states
to provide both military and civilian personnel.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. could no longer carry the burden of peace-keeping
alone and needed regional organizations to help carry out the
responsibility, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Cooperation between the U.N. and regional organizations has
become the hallmark of today's peace-keeping, " he noted.
</P>
</TEXT>
