Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Bin Mubarak made the statement after a meeting with Arab
League Secretary General Esmat Abdel-Meguid. The Bahraini official
arrived in Cairo earlier in the day to accompany Emir Sheikh Hamad
Bin Isa al-Khalifa in a visit to Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Bin Mubarak, meanwhile, called for full preparations for
the possible summit in a bid to achieve tangible results to
enhance Arab solidarity and forge a united Arab stance on the
Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
