Israel's Labor Party, in his country's elections last month,
Mubarak proposed with Moroccan King Hassan II during a recent
visit to the North African country that a summit be held to
coordinate and adopt a unified stance toward the peace talks with
the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
The possible summit should also discuss other key issues
related to the Arab world, including restoring Arab solidarity,
Mubarak maintained.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Bin Mubarak said he also discussed with Abdel-Meguid the
issues on the agenda of the Arab Foreign Ministers Council due to
meet in September. The Arab countries convene meetings of the
council in March and September each year.
</P>
<P>
He voiced hope that the coming meetings would reach the
required settlement of several pressing Arab issues which he did
not elaborate. 
