<HEADLINE> S. Africa's GDP Increases in 1st Quarter of 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 21 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's gross domestic
product (GDP) rose by 0.4 percent in the first quarter of 1999
compared with the fourth quarter of 1998, Statistics South Africa
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
A new system based on international standards was used for the
first time to peg the GDP in the country, the organization said.
</P>
<P>
It said the GDP, from which the quarterly real growth rates and
the annual real growth rates are derived, was now based on the
latest conventions of the United Nations-prescribed System of
National Accounts.
</P>
<P>
The method pushes GDP level upward by a few percentage points
through counting certain activities into GDP for the first time,
the organization said. It incorporated new concepts and
definitions and re-defined various activities as part of GDP.
</P>
</TEXT>
