<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Licenses 5th Foreign Oil Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Investment
Authority announced that the German and Yemeni Joint
Trans-Boundary Company has been licensed to establish a 5.6
million U.S. dollars worth oil supplying and distributing firm in
Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The newly licensed company, which has vast experience in Europe
and Asia, is the fifth foreign petroleum distributing company in
Ethiopia next to Mobil, Shell, Agip and Total, state media
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The company would build a depot with a capacity of at least
5,000 cubic meters, oil distribution stations and oil filling
stations in seven regions of the Horn of Africa country, the
investment authority was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The newly licensed company will supply and distribute
petroleum, petroleum products and liquefied petroleum gas which is
used as fuel for cooking, the authority added.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia is a non-oil producing country and depends all
petroleum products on import through Djibouti port. 
</P>
