<HEADLINE> Major S. African Banks Cut Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 21 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's major banks
announced Monday that they are cutting their prime lending and
home loan rates by one percentage point from 19 to 18 percent.
</P>
<P>
Standard Bank, Nedcor, ABSA, First National Bank, and BOE said
that they would reduce their rates Friday.
</P>
<P>
The cut in interest rates has been on the cards for some time
and comes on the back of strengthening of the South African
currency rand and the news Monday that the economy is beginning to
grow again.
</P>
<P>
Economists expect further cuts before the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
The gross domestic product (GDP) grew by 0.4 percent in the
first quarter of 1999, following negative growth in the last two
quarters of 1998, Statistics South Africa announced Monday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
