<HEADLINE> Bahraini Emir Arrives in Egypt for Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Bahraini Emir Sheikh Hamad Bin Isa
al-Khalifa said on Monday that his visit to Egypt is part of the
continued coordination between the two countries on bilateral ties
and regional issues.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Hamad made the remarks upon his arrival at the Cairo
International Airport for his first visit to Egypt after he
assumed power in March after the death of his father.
</P>
<P>
Stressing that he will follow his father's suit in
strengthening ties with Egypt, Sheikh Hamad said his meeting with
President Hosni Mubarak will augur well and hopefully turn for the
interests of Bahrain, Egypt, and the Arab nation.
</P>
<P>
The constant changes on the international and Arab arenas
"necessitate intensifying meetings and consultations among Arab
brothers" in a bid to reach coordination and cooperation, which
will help realize the supreme national and joint interests, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Following the victory of Ehud Barak, moderate leader of
Israel's Labor Party, in his country's elections on May 17, Arabs
are talking about holding a summit to coordinate stances on the
Mideast peace process. Bahrain has expressed support for the
proposal put forward recently by Mubarak.
</P>
<P>
"Restoring and deepening Arab solidarity should be a priority
in this stage of the Arab national march, a stage that calls on
all of us to stand up to surrounding challenges," he underlined.
</P>
<P>
The Bahraini emir voiced appreciation for Egypt's role in
supporting his country's development at all levels, saying that he
was satisfied with the achievements made by the two countries in
the economic and trade cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
