<HEADLINE> Pak, India Continue Shelling Each Other: Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani and Indian armies
continued shelling each other in the past 24 hours and casualties
were reported from both sides.
</P>
<P>
According to a Pakistani military spokesman Monday, Pakistan's
artillery units, in revenge shelling, effectively struck India's
logistic installations, military convoys and other targets in
Drass, Kargil and Batlik sectors.
</P>
<P>
He said that according to credible information, 13 Indian
soldiers were killed and numerous wounded.
</P>
<P>
An Indian fuel storage depot and several vehicles were also
destroyed in the shelling and "their smoldering debris could be
seen burning from miles away."
</P>
<P>
Giving details of India's "unprovoked and indiscriminate"
shelling in the past day, the spokesman stated the Indian Army
again targeted innocent civilians at Dudnial, Kot Katerah and
adjoining areas, during which one person was killed while seven
others, including two women, received serious injuries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
