<HEADLINE> Vietnamese President Begins Visit in Laos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese President Tran Duc Luong
held talks with Lao leaders in Vientiane, the Lao capital, on
Monday during which the two sides agreed to further promote their
special friendship and comprehensive cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Luong arrived in Vientiane on Monday morning for a five-day
official friendship visit to Laos at the invitation of Lao
President Khamtay Siphandone.
</P>
<P>
On Monday Luong had separate talks with Siphandone, Lao
National Assembly President Saman Vinhaket and Prime Minister
Sisavat Keobounphan, Vietnam News Agency said.
</P>
<P>
Vignaketh expressed his hope that the special friendship and
comprehensive cooperation between the two countries and their
national assemblies would further develop as a result of the visit
by Luong.
</P>
<P>
Luong informed Vignaketh of the outcome of his talks with
Siphandone. He said the two sides devised measures to boost their
multi-faceted cooperation covering all socio-economic development
aspects.
</P>
<P>
Luong affirmed the determination of the Communist Party,
government, and people of Vietnam to unceasingly strengthen and
push forward the special relationship and comprehensive
cooperation between Vietnam and Laos fostered by late Vietnamese
President Ho Chi Minh and late Lao President Kaysome Phomvihane.
</P>
</TEXT>
